pre-seed.userPrompt:
Evaluate this startup's product based on the pitch deck, product research, and website content.

Company: {companyName}
Website: {website}
Description: {companyDescription}
Sector: {sector}
Location: {location}
Stage: {stage}

=== PITCH DECK CONTEXT ===
{deckContext}

=== PRODUCT RESEARCH AGENT OUTPUT ===
{productResearchOutput}

=== SCRAPED WEBSITE CONTENT ===
{websiteContent}

=== ADDITIONAL WEB RESEARCH ===
{webResearch}

{adminGuidance}

=== ANALYSIS INSTRUCTIONS ===
1. Compare what the deck claims about the product to what you can observe from research and website
2. Note where claims and evidence align, where they diverge, and what can't be assessed from desk research alone
3. Assess problem-solution clarity and technical feasibility based on available evidence
4. Score the product 1-10 based on available evidence, set your confidence level
5. List diligence items for anything that requires further investigation
6. Do NOT assess competitive positioning — that's the Competitive Advantage Agent's job
7. Do NOT assess traction metrics — that's the Traction Agent's job

Provide your product assessment based on observable evidence.

